1
00:00:01,060 --> 00:00:08,840
Fairy Tail has been completely absorbed 
by the hyperspace magic Anima,

2
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:12,740
which was used by an alternate world Edolas

3
00:00:12,740 --> 00:00:15,630
that has begun to lose its magic power.

4
00:00:15,630 --> 00:00:22,600
Natsu, Happy, Wendy, and Carla have headed 
to Edolas to rescue their friends,

5
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:26,140
where they meet the members 
of the Edolas Fairy Tail.

6
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:32,510
Plus, Edolas's Erza is a 
captain in the Royal Army,

7
00:00:32,510 --> 00:00:36,680
but is also known by the 
title "Fairy Hunter Erza".

8
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:14,870
This is Edolas's Fairy Tail.

9
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,200
So, what again?

10
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:20,040
You came from another world 
called Earthland, then...

11
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:23,080
And you came to Edolas in 
order to rescue your friends?

12
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:23,990
Right.

13
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:27,110
And there's a Fairy Tail in that world, too?

14
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:29,790
And Erza is on your side over there?

15
00:02:30,170 --> 00:02:31,550
Basically, yes.

16
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:32,170
Aye.

17
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:35,140
That's not so easy to swallow.

18
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:41,070
But it's true that this Natsu 
isn't the Natsu we know.

19
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:43,400
The only thing they have in 
common is the way they look.

20
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:44,430
You can say that again.

21
00:02:49,690 --> 00:02:51,030
Key of Hope.

22
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:57,150
This girl is who I am in that other world?

23
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,420
Hello...

24
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,900
You're all tiny, Wendy!

25
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:04,570
Anyway, we'd like you to tell 
us how to get to the Royal City.

26
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:11,500
Our friends have been sucked 
up by this world's king!

27
00:03:11,970 --> 00:03:14,750
If we don't rescue them soon, everyone 
will be converted into magic power...

28
00:03:15,930 --> 00:03:17,630
They'll be gone forever!

29
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:21,900
Sorry to tell you, li'l me, but 
you'd be better off stopping now.

30
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,790
Go against Edolas's king, 
and you forfeit your lives.

31
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:30,050
That's just how powerful the kingdom is.

32
00:03:31,930 --> 00:03:35,240
Magic power is limited in this 
world. It's not infinite.

33
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:38,100
To put it another way, it'll 
be used up eventually.

34
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:42,510
Fearing that, the King of Edolas 
tried to monopolize all magic.

35
00:03:43,110 --> 00:03:44,530
Isn't that right, Juvia-chan?

36
00:03:46,090 --> 00:03:50,200
Due to that, all Wizard Guilds 
were ordered to disband.

37
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:54,450
Everyone resisted at first.

38
00:03:54,450 --> 00:03:58,700
But one after another were crushed before 
the might of the Royal Army's magic regiments.

39
00:03:59,390 --> 00:04:01,050
This is the only guild that is left.

40
00:04:01,390 --> 00:04:03,520
And of course, we haven't 
been spared casualties.

41
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,480
We've lost almost half our members.

42
00:04:06,910 --> 00:04:08,170
The master, as well...

43
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:09,980
Damn it all...

44
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:15,130
It takes all we got just to 
keep one step ahead of them!

45
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:17,200
So you should stay away.

46
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:19,390
Go back to your world.

47
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,280
Please. Tell us the way.

48
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,070
I will save my friends.

49
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:28,770
No matter what.

50
00:04:46,050 --> 00:04:48,450
This is the Royal City of Edolas.

51
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:51,580
The United Chiefs of Staff.

52
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:55,170
Whoa!

53
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:55,910
Whoa!

54
00:04:55,910 --> 00:04:58,540
Check out that giant lacrima!

55
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:00,150
I saw when it got here, Hughes.

56
00:05:00,730 --> 00:05:01,890
It's quite pretty, yes.

57
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,400
That's like tens of thousands 
of Earthland people's magic!

58
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:09,900
More precisely, one should say, it's 
the magical power of about 100 wizards,

59
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,850
plus a great deal of other living things.

60
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,330
Don't sweat the details, Sugar Boy!

61
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:20,770
What I was tryin' to say, 
was how it was like, whoa!

62
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:26,440
This man is Captain of the Third Magic 
Regiment of the Royal Army, Hughes.

63
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:32,950
And similarly, he is Captain of the Fourth 
Magic Regiment of the Royal Army, Sugar Boy.

64
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:38,960
Finally, the Captain of the Second Magic 
Regiment of the Royal Army, Erza Knightwalker.

65
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,690
Also known as Fairy Hunter Erza.

66
00:05:44,630 --> 00:05:45,400
Listen, dudes...

67
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:48,190
When I say "whoa", it ain't like, kinda whoa.

68
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:49,700
It's like, whoa whoa.

69
00:05:50,780 --> 00:05:52,160
Whoa, indeed.

70
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:56,760
Mizz Erza, have you not 
yet done in Fairy Tail?

71
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:57,540
Byro!

72
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,090
You're starting to give the designation 
"Fairy Hunter" a bad name...

73
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:06,730
This man is the Chief of Staff 
of the Royal Army, Byro.

74
00:06:07,490 --> 00:06:11,130
The only guild left iz now Fairy Tail.

75
00:06:11,130 --> 00:06:15,010
Well, they are the guild 
that runz the fastest.

76
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:18,600
But our highnezz will be 
expecting results soon.

77
00:06:20,780 --> 00:06:24,770
Don't be hasty. The day our goddess 
catches her Fairy prey will come soon.

78
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,270
That's right!

79
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:29,950
Erza's sword is like, whoa, man! Whoa!

80
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:34,670
Stop laughing in that freaky manner, Byro.

81
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,810
Panther Lily.

82
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:39,230
I do not like those with loud mouths.

83
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:42,290
That includes you, Hughes.

84
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:48,330
This man is Captain of the First Magic 
Regiment of the Royal Army, Panther Lily.

85
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,550
What, me too?

86
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:54,140
I bet you think this is more 
like, whoa, than any of us!

87
00:06:54,970 --> 00:06:56,510
Shut your mouth for a bit.

88
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,960
Not in a good mood, Lily?

89
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:07,400
He doesn't seem pleased with 
the recent military buildup.

90
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:10,410
He should have welcomed 
it as a military man...

91
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:14,150
However, our kingdom basically 
encompasses the entire world.

92
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:18,040
It is true that there is no obvious reason 
for a further strengthening of the army.

93
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,080
Isn't it because there are still 
a few pockets of resistance?

94
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,680
If that were it, we alone 
would easily suffice.

95
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:27,880
I don't get it!

96
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,080
Whoa man, this is all so like, complicated...

97
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,600
I don't get it!

98
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:38,180
Your highness!

99
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:40,560
Your highness!

100
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:44,060
Your highness!

101
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,380
We will be able to extract magic power

102
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:51,360
from the giant lacrima after 
4 days, right on schedule!

103
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:56,240
This girl is the Aide to the Chief 
of Staff of the Royal Army, Coco.

104
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:57,540
We did it!

105
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:00,450
Not enough...

106
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,710
Your highness, what did you just say?

107
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:11,310
I said it was not enough.

108
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:13,250
If I may, your highness...

109
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:17,380
That lacrima represents the magic 
power of an entire Earthland city!

110
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:21,870
It's enough to power the kingdom's 
magic for the next 10 years!

111
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:27,060
Our great kingdom of Edolas 
must have no limits.

112
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:30,410
Give it to us...

113
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,980
Give more magic power to us...

114
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:36,000
What I seek is eternity!

115
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,580
An endless supply of magic power!

116
00:08:39,780 --> 00:08:43,840
And this man is the king of Edolas, Faust!

117
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:51,420
Okay... Stay right there...

118
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,950
Hold it!

119
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,050
What is he doing?

120
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:02,200
I wonder how much longer 'til 
we get to the Royal City...

121
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,390
We just left, remember?

122
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:06,500
And they told us it would 
take 5 days to walk there.

123
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:11,570
Our Aera aren't working properly, 
so we have no choice but to walk.

124
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,700
Can we really not use magic anymore?

125
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:16,860
I don't know.

126
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,890
But it doesn't bode well...

127
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:27,650
Happy, help out!

128
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:29,820
I've never seen a frog like this before.

129
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,950
I'll bring it back as a present for Lucy!

130
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:34,360
I don't think she'll like it.

131
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:40,950
It's huge!

132
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:45,290
Natsu, it's attacking!

133
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,470
All right!

134
00:09:46,470 --> 00:09:47,720
Fist of the...

135
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:55,300
I forgot I can't use magic!

136
00:09:59,690 --> 00:10:02,250
Yup! I can't use magic, either!

137
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:07,380
In that case, I'll do it even without magic!

138
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,090
Natsu?

139
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,490
Scary Lucy!

140
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:30,070
Scary Lucy-san!

141
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:32,060
Quit calling me "scary"!

142
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:38,110
That guy wasn't much.

143
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:39,740
But why are you here?

144
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,290
It's... not like I was worried 
about you, or anything.

145
00:10:46,770 --> 00:10:50,210
You say a lot of stuff, but 
you're Lucy, all right.

146
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,160
How does that follow exactly?

147
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,750
See, those kinds of lines are totally "Lucy".

148
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:57,060
I wanna show Lucy this scary Lucy.

149
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:59,130
I can't wait to see the look 
on the real one's face!

150
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:01,100
So I'm a fake?!

151
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:04,940
Technique 12: The Back-Crack Bridge!

152
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,770
Yup, she's scary all right.

153
00:11:07,770 --> 00:11:09,900
Can this continue for 5 days?

154
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:12,880
I can tell it's going to 
be hard going... Seriously.

155
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:17,580
Crap.

156
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:20,110
I've been thrown to one whacked out place.

157
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:23,200
Sheesh... This is messed up.

158
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:36,000
I see. They thought you were 
Exceeds, and reported it.

159
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,630
That's what drew them to us.

160
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:40,650
I still can't believe that Erza's our enemy.

161
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:43,800
Well, either one's scary, though.

162
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,530
Oh?

163
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:46,750
No, no... I was talking about Erza!

164
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:51,600
To us, what's unbelievable is that 
we could ever get along with Erza.

165
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,350
Mysterious, isn't it?

166
00:11:53,710 --> 00:11:55,980
There isn't a wizard out 
there who doesn't fear her.

167
00:11:56,430 --> 00:11:58,040
Just seeing her face means certain death.

168
00:11:58,540 --> 00:12:00,450
I <i>really</i> don't want to run into her.

169
00:12:00,450 --> 00:12:02,320
The one I know is scary enough!

170
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:05,300
Look, we're here. Can you see it?

171
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,120
It's a city, Happy!

172
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,660
Walking for days sure was tough.

173
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:12,750
The buildings are kind of round?

174
00:12:13,450 --> 00:12:14,810
Let's hurry.

175
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,580
Thank you so much for coming with us.

176
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:19,760
F-Follow me.

177
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:23,840
You won't be able to go any farther 
without some magic weapons.

178
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:26,200
Thanks a bunch, Scary Lucy!

179
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,250
Scary Lucy!

180
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,850
You pickin' a fight?!

181
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:32,370
This is the city of Louen.

182
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,750
Until a little while ago, magic 
was bought and sold normally.

183
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:42,700
But now, with the kingdom's Guild Hunt, 
trafficking in magic is forbidden.

184
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:46,350
And that's not all. Even 
possessing it is a crime.

185
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:50,120
Just possessing it is a crime?

186
00:12:50,430 --> 00:12:52,980
What happened to the people 
who could always use it?

187
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,010
What?

188
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:57,430
You just make sure not 
to have it on you, right?

189
00:12:57,830 --> 00:13:01,250
And wait, what do you mean people 
who could always use magic?

190
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:08,300
It looks like in this 
world, magic is an object.

191
00:13:08,570 --> 00:13:09,540
Object?

192
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:11,580
By saying that magic is limited here,

193
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:15,940
it means that there aren't people like us 
who hold magic within their own bodies.

194
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:19,780
Physical objects like lacrima 
can hold magic power.

195
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:24,750
So if you combine them with weapons or 
other daily items, you create magic items.

196
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:27,990
That's referred to generally as "magic".

197
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:31,720
So the wizards over here 
just use magic items?

198
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:32,790
I suppose.

199
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:34,540
We're here.

200
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:37,510
There's a magic black 
market underground here.

201
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,860
You'll need it if you want to travel.

202
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:41,290
Black market?

203
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:45,970
Guess we gotta play by the 
rules here to use magic.

204
00:13:45,970 --> 00:13:46,680
Aye.

205
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,790
You adapt quick.

206
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:57,250
At the same time, another Earthland 
wizard can be seen entering Louen.

207
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:01,440
So then, where should I start?

208
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:04,260
Guess I should get it over with and ask.

209
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:12,400
Hey. I'd like to ask you something.

210
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:15,540
Hey, wait!

211
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:25,810
This Edolas place don't got 
a lot of friendly people, do it?

212
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:36,710
Looks like there's always some kiddies 
rarin' to play with me though, no matter where I go.

213
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:40,750
You got a problem with us, bud?

214
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,270
You damn fly!

215
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:45,150
Damn fly? Me?

216
00:14:45,690 --> 00:14:48,260
Ain't nobody else here but you!

217
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:50,010
If ya don't like "fly", how about "maggot"?

218
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:52,980
I'm not laughing.

219
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,620
Y-You bastard!

220
00:15:01,180 --> 00:15:03,220
Ow!

221
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:09,970
A huge lacrima showed up recently.

222
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,100
Where is it?

223
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,520
Spit it out!

224
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,980
I-I don't know!

225
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:16,550
Is that so?

226
00:15:17,380 --> 00:15:18,850
Then you get a second helping...

227
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:22,140
Wait! We really don't know!

228
00:15:22,140 --> 00:15:23,240
Right? Right?

229
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,100
Yeah, yeah...

230
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:25,950
Fine, then.

231
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:27,600
I'll ask someone else.

232
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,940
Get lost, you guys.

233
00:15:31,470 --> 00:15:34,850
Wait, Gajeel, since when 
did you get so strong?

234
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:35,610
Yeah.

235
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,450
I mean, until just recently, 
you'd never get in a fight.

236
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:44,460
Could it be another me that's here in Edolas?

237
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,560
Tell me, what's the Gajeel here do?

238
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:48,670
Huh?

239
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,250
I just happen to look like him.

240
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:52,320
You're joking, right?

241
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,890
You look identical.

242
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,350
Whatever, just answer me.

243
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:57,540
What does Gajeel usually do?

244
00:15:57,970 --> 00:16:01,350
He's a freelance writer here in 
Edolas with a terrible reputation.

245
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,410
Writer?

246
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:06,810
All he does is write articles in magazines 
and newspapers criticizing the kingdom.

247
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:09,730
That's why he's hated by 
all the people in town.

248
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:13,200
So that's why no one would talk with me.

249
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,800
A freelance writer, huh?

250
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,540
I kinda want to meet this guy.

251
00:16:21,050 --> 00:16:23,730
There's a whole lot of 
iffy-looking things lined up.

252
00:16:23,730 --> 00:16:26,170
This shop stinks of mold.

253
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:31,980
That's because we have some antique 
items with a long history!

254
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:37,340
Mold, damage, smell... It's all part 
of their mystique, dear customers.

255
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:39,690
I don't care about mystique.

256
00:16:39,690 --> 00:16:42,010
All I care about is whether they're useful.

257
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:45,160
There's a bunch of imitations out there, 
so be real careful when you buy anything.

258
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,860
Hey, old dude, you got any fire magic?

259
00:16:49,570 --> 00:16:52,310
In that case, I have just the thing!

260
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:54,280
How about this?

261
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,550
Edolas magic, flaming sword!

262
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:58,140
You charge it here, and then...

263
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,650
Look! Amazing, yes?

264
00:17:00,650 --> 00:17:03,290
That flame's pretty weak, but 
it's better than nothing.

265
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,510
Sir, you have very good taste!

266
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:07,210
I like this.

267
00:17:07,210 --> 00:17:08,370
What's good about it?

268
00:17:08,370 --> 00:17:10,200
It's small and cute!

269
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,630
Um, look here. Choosing like that 
isn't going to do us any good.

270
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,600
That's called an Air Bullet Gun.

271
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:20,680
It looks like a cute container on the 
outside, but if you open it a little like this...

272
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,740
Wind Magic!

273
00:17:25,740 --> 00:17:27,300
How romantic.

274
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,030
Madam, you have very good taste!

275
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:30,640
Okay, we'll take these two.

276
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:33,060
Thank you very much!

277
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:38,050
Each of them is 20,000, but I'll give you a 
deal and let you have them for 18,000 each!

278
00:17:38,650 --> 00:17:40,110
That's pretty expensive...

279
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:42,790
Wares are getting scarce, 
so they're quite valuable...

280
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:45,410
Wait, aren't we forgetting 
something important?

281
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,820
Do you have any money?

282
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:49,890
Of course not!

283
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,410
This isn't a laughing matter!

284
00:17:51,410 --> 00:17:54,000
All I have in my pocket are some biscuits.

285
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,820
Lucy, pay the man.

286
00:17:56,950 --> 00:18:00,000
Being pressured like this... 
Maybe I kind of like it?

287
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:01,760
Something the matter?

288
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,300
Fine then!

289
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:05,060
I'll treat you.

290
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:08,860
No, no! I can't take money 
from you, Lucy-sama!

291
00:18:09,170 --> 00:18:12,380
You really saved me when those 
hoodlums showed up that time.

292
00:18:12,630 --> 00:18:15,400
Naw, that wasn't anything much.

293
00:18:15,810 --> 00:18:19,570
Anyway, consider them a present from me!

294
00:18:20,170 --> 00:18:21,850
Great, we'll take them with our thanks.

295
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:24,040
Thanks, old dude!

296
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:29,000
Unlike our Lucy, Scary 
Lucy is really dependable!

297
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,290
I told you not to call me scary!

298
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:35,020
You've got a lot of pull around here.

299
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:36,550
You've really saved us.

300
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:38,250
By the way...

301
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:42,730
I'm kind of interested in hearing 
about the Lucy over there...

302
00:18:48,990 --> 00:18:51,430
I'm writing a novel?!

303
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:55,770
I'm from a rich family, and use key magic?

304
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:59,270
Both of you are equally noisy, though.

305
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:00,900
Don't call me noisy!

306
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:03,930
We just bought this... But how do I use it?

307
00:19:04,190 --> 00:19:06,260
You stupid... Don't show magic 
in front of other people!

308
00:19:07,180 --> 00:19:10,660
I told you that magic was banned 
around the world right now, remember?

309
00:19:10,970 --> 00:19:11,910
I'm sorry...

310
00:19:12,370 --> 00:19:15,950
But magic used to be part 
of your daily lives, right?

311
00:19:16,810 --> 00:19:17,500
Yes.

312
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:21,550
The bastards from the kingdom have 
stolen away a part of our culture.

313
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:23,090
But why?

314
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,850
So they can monopolize it.

315
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:31,360
Then if we beat the people from the kingdom, 
magic might come back to the world, right?

316
00:19:31,790 --> 00:19:33,480
Do you understand how crazy that sounds?

317
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:35,980
There's no way to fight the Royal Army!

318
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:38,510
Then why did you follow us?

319
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,590
Because I wanted to tell you 
how to get to the Royal City.

320
00:19:43,570 --> 00:19:45,460
I wasn't planning to fight or anything...

321
00:19:46,230 --> 00:19:47,900
Okay, then! Thanks a lot.

322
00:19:51,170 --> 00:19:52,010
There they are!

323
00:19:52,010 --> 00:19:53,730
Seal off the entrance to the city!

324
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:54,770
The Royal Army!

325
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,030
You're wizards from Fairy Tail, yes?

326
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,300
Stay right there!

327
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:00,600
We've already been discovered?

328
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:06,510
Okay, then!

329
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,700
Let's try this sucker out!

330
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:09,220
Don't!

331
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,680
Let's go!

332
00:20:10,870 --> 00:20:12,100
Fire!

333
00:20:12,410 --> 00:20:15,050
Carla, how do I use this again?!

334
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:15,980
How should I know?

335
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:20,690
Shields?

336
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,860
One more!

337
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,190
Magic power is limited, remember?

338
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:29,000
All magic has a certain number 
of times it can be used!

339
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,040
Just once?!

340
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:34,160
If you keep the output in mind, 
you can use it about 100 times!

341
00:20:34,220 --> 00:20:36,170
Capture them!

342
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,190
Um... Um...

343
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,190
This is bad!

344
00:20:46,690 --> 00:20:48,210
What have you done, Wendy?

345
00:20:48,210 --> 00:20:49,660
I'm sorry!

346
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,020
Over there! Capture them at all costs!

347
00:20:58,250 --> 00:20:58,690
Yes, sir!

348
00:21:05,650 --> 00:21:09,030
We've managed to avoid them, but we won't 
be able to leave the city at this rate.

349
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:11,530
The magic here is hard to use.

350
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:12,700
Yeah...

351
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,230
What'll we do?

352
00:21:14,230 --> 00:21:15,760
Isn't there another entrance?

353
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,540
We're in trouble...

354
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,780
We found you, Fairy Tail!

355
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,070
Let me go!

356
00:21:23,070 --> 00:21:23,380
Huh?

357
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:25,050
Come with us!

358
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,790
You're Lucy, right?

359
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:30,650
Yes, I'm Lucy, but what's going on here?

360
00:21:30,650 --> 00:21:31,750
Lucy!

361
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,470
Me?

362
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,180
That hurts, sheesh!

363
00:21:34,550 --> 00:21:36,440
Why is Lucy here?

364
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,940
W-What's going on?

365
00:21:38,230 --> 00:21:39,150
Man...

366
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:39,900
I have to save her!

367
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:41,880
Hey!

368
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:45,360
Gate of the Scorpion, I open thee!

369
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:48,700
Lucy-san, we can't use magic in this world!

370
00:21:49,140 --> 00:21:50,070
Scorpio!

371
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:53,900
We are!

372
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:57,590
Sandbuster!

373
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:02,170
Magic?

374
00:22:02,170 --> 00:22:02,840
How?

375
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:04,670
T-That's...

376
00:22:05,110 --> 00:22:08,200
I'm going on a date with Aquarius now.

377
00:22:08,350 --> 00:22:08,780
Later.

378
00:22:09,820 --> 00:22:10,430
Lucy...

379
00:22:11,950 --> 00:22:12,920
You guys!

380
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:14,750
I missed you!

381
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,140
Somebody explain what's going on...

382
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:16,810
Aye...

383
00:22:19,330 --> 00:22:20,940
Me?!

384
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:59,350
Happy, how much longer until 
the Edolas me shows up?

385
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:01,620
Don't ask me...

386
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:03,970
What are you going to 
do when he does, anyway?

387
00:24:03,970 --> 00:24:06,650
We could have a contest to see 
whose flames are hotter...

388
00:24:07,020 --> 00:24:08,920
Or to see who's stronger, etc...

389
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:09,880
There's plenty of possibilities!

390
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,510
Natsu, we didn't come here to play.

391
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:13,760
You know that, right?

392
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:16,260
Next time: Fireball!

393
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:20,210
I know, I know! I don't 
plan on losing, after all.

394
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:21,520
I'll fight him totally seriously!

395
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:24,760
That's not what I meant. But whatever!

396
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:26,760


